ce:section.ce:para:
Ochratoxin A (OTA) with high toxicity has been listed as a group 2B carcinogen by the International Agency for Research on Cancer (IARC) (Wei et al., 2019, Zhu et al., 2020). Herein, a S doped carbon dots modified gold nanoparticles (S-CDs/AuNPs) with MeHg+-stimulated POD-like activity was fabricated for OTA assay. The POD-like activity of gold amalgamation (Au@HgNPs) was studied in detail, which was discovered as an efficient colorimetric and surface-enhanced Raman scattering (SERS) probe for the selective detection of OTA. The S-CDs/AuNPs with weak POD-like activity was used to both catalyze the reduction of MeHg+ to Hg0 to form Au@HgNPs, thereby enhancing POD-like activity and SERS enhancement. The Au@HgNPs displayed excellent POD-like activity to catalyze TMB into blue oxTMB, showing high density of ‘hot-spot’. Thus, both the chromogenic and SERS signals were simultaneously turned on. Moreover, after the addition of OTA, Au@HgNPs could result in the simultaneous shutdown color rendering and SERS signals by providing hydrogen bonding and coordination bonds sites for capturing OTA molecules (
                     Scheme 1

                     ).
